hes can be renewed without removal of the damping cylinder. ","Clamp ","service tool T3880171"," in a vice and mount the fork vertically in the service tool.","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool","Fork","Top cap","Never tightly clamp the fork outer tube as this will cause the tube to permanently distort. A distorted tube is not serviceable and must be replaced.","The top cap is not under spring tension and will not spring upwards when the threads disengage.","Use ","service tool T3880800"," to unscrew the top cap until it is released from the fork outer tube.","With the aid of an assistant, compress the spring by hand to gain access to the lock nut. Insert the plate from ","service tool T3880067"," in between the spring and lock nut.","Fork top cap","Washer","Damper rod lock nut","Plate from ","service tool T3880067","Spring","Loosen the lock nut for the top cap by a small amount.","Carefully count the number of turns necessary and unscrew the top cap until the top cap is released from the damper.","Keep the top cap and damping adjuster rod assembly aligned with the fork tube to prevent damage to the adjuster rod during the stage that follows.","Remove the top cap, washer and damping adjuster rod assembly.","Release the plate from ","service tool T3880067"," from the fork.","Remove the spring from the fork assembly.","The spring spacer will fall out of the fork when you invert the fork in the stage that follows.","Holding the fork inner and outer tubes together, invert the fork and pour out the fork oil into a suitable container. Pump the damper rod to remove all of the oil.","Fork Seal and Bearing Bush Removal","Invert the fork assembly and mount it in ","service tool T3880171",".","Raise the fork inner tube and remove the dust seal from the fork outer tube.","Inverted fork","Dust seal","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool","Remove the circlip.","Circlip","Remove the fork from ","service tool T3880171"," and, using a slide hammer action to release the oil seal and bearing bushe